2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 87
BY SENATOR HODGES
A RESOLUTION
To commend Lacie Thomas Fontenot for being named the 2026 Louisiana School Health
Service Provider of the Year by the Louisiana Department of Education.
WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot is a state and nationally certified speech-language
pathologist, who has faithfully served students within Livingston Parish Public Schools for
more than twelve years; and
WHEREAS, throughout her tenure, Lacie Fontenot has provided exceptional speech
and language services to students in Livingston Parish, including at Live Oak Middle School
and Live Oak Junior High, helping countless young people develop the skills necessary to
communicate effectively and succeed academically and socially; and
WHEREAS, in recognition of her exemplary dedication and impact, Lacie Fontenot
has been honored as the 2026 Louisiana School Health Service Provider of the Year by the
Louisiana Department of Education, a distinction that reflects both professional excellence
and meaningful contributions to student health and development; and
WHEREAS, through the School Health Provider of the Year program, the Louisiana
Department of Education recognizes and celebrates some of Louisiana's most exceptional
school health providers; and
WHEREAS, this program provides an opportunity to acknowledge providers who
demonstrate superior health services in schools and support the expansion of those services;
and
WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot's service extends well beyond the traditional
responsibilities of a speech-language pathologist and demonstrates a deep and abiding
commitment to the school community; and
WHEREAS, she has taken a leadership role in organizing the Angel Tree project,
helping to provide Christmas gifts and support for students and families in need, all while
fostering a spirit of generosity and care within the school community; and
