WHEREAS, Lacie Fontenot also dedicates her time overseeing the school's
self-sustained food pantry, working diligently to provide weekend food bags for students
facing food insecurity, and ensuring that basic needs are met so that students are better able
to focus on their education; and
WHEREAS, through her compassion, initiative, and unwavering dedication, Lacie
Fontenot exemplifies the highest ideals of public service and serves as a role model for
students, educators, and health service providers in the state.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend Lacie Thomas Fontenot on being named the 2026 Louisiana School
Health Service Provider of the Year and does hereby express sincere appreciation for her
outstanding contributions to the students and families of Livingston Parish and the state of
Louisiana.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Lacie
Thomas Fontenot.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
